snippet: The current race for mayor, between a Latino Democrat and a business-oriented Republican, is in many ways a fight for San Diego’s political soul.
abstract: Mayor’s race in San Diego between Latino Democrat David Alvarez and business-oriented Republican Kevin Faulconer is in many ways a fight for city's political soul; for years, moderate Republican leaders have transformed downtown into a model of urban redevelopment, but many Democrats argue that business-focused elite have neglected and ignored working-class neighborhoods.
lead_paragraph: The current race for mayor, between a Latino Democrat and a business-oriented Republican, is in many ways a fight for San Diego’s political soul.

headline.main: A Battle of Ideology in a City Unaccustomed to That Sort of Election
headline.print_headline: A Battle of Ideology in a City Unaccustomed to That Sort of Election
